    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractHiLoLongIdGenerator

        public AbstractHiLoLongIdGenerator​(HiValueGenerator hiValueGenerator,
                                   long loUpperBoundOpen)
        Parameters:
        hiValueGenerator - A hi value generator. It must be ThreadSafe is this implementation of AbstractHiLoLongIdGenerator is ThreadSafe. If hiValueGenerator is persistent, then the constructed AbstractHiLoLongIdGenerator is persistent.
        loUpperBoundOpen - This parameter specifies how many identifiers we can generate after obtaining a new hi value without retrieving the next hi value again.

        Generally speaking, loUpperBoundOpen can be safely increased for the same source of hi values. But decreasing it requires caution and in case of using a database sequence for generating hi values (a persistent generator) requires advancing the sequence value far enough to maintain the guarantee of identifier uniqueness.

    • Method Detail

      • calculateId

        protected static final long calculateId​(long hi,
                                        long lo,
                                        long loUpperBoundOpen)
        Calculates an identifier.
        Parameters:
        hi - A hi value, which in practical cases may represent a value from a database sequence.
        lo - A lo value which is a looped in-memory counter. lo ∈ [0; loUpperBoundOpen).
        loUpperBoundOpen - See AbstractHiLoLongIdGenerator(HiValueGenerator, long).
        Returns:
        The identifier corresponding to the supplied hi and lo, which uniquely define the identifier for a given loUpperBoundOpen.
